\i \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
weltenschauung 
\i0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
or worldview (Goetz 2008); a quasi-religion (Plantinga); a set of procedural methodological and substantive ontological commitments, a set of methodological commitments alone (Jacobs; Rea 2013). It has been maligned as scientism but also celebrated as scientism (Rosenburg 2011). Very loosely, naturalistic philosophers value the scientific method or methods above all others, including a priori philosophizing. Also, some or most naturalistic philosophers are anti-theists. Theism is the tradition that rivals naturalism (Murphy 2013). \

